fields.description:
I'd like to suggest making the "Allow anyone to join" option at code review form to be enabled by default and non-configurable. 
Let such behavior be optional (and could be activated somewhere in the "default reviewers" section of crucible project config ), and have ability to:
1) work as before;
2) work with per-project forced permission for anyone to join reviews;

Currently when setting up a Crucible review that involves reviewing files between two tags (which is the majority of the time for us) you have to use EyeQL in the following manner:

{code}
select revisions 
from dir /Path/To/Project where not tagged <=START_TAG and tagged <= END_TAG
{code}

It would be very beneficial to have this functionality in the _Manage Files_ portion of the UI when creating a new crucible request so that a user would have the ability to simply input starting and end tags instead of having to go through the _Advanced Search_.
